[An earlier more limited comparison of American Indian/Alaskan native
hospitalised patients with hospitalised patients from the general
population of Anchorage (see ProMED-mail Influenza pandemic (H1N1) 2009
(118): USA (AK) ethnicity 20091201.4108) concluded that ethnicity might be
a factor influencing the severity of response to infection by the pandemic
(H1N1) 2009 influenza virus. In both groups, however, asthma was identified
as the principal predisposing factor in development of severe disease.
Information on obesity was not reported, but should also be considered as a
predisposing factor. - Mod.CP]
